@startuml
actor Patient
participant "Web App" as Web
participant "API" as API
participant "Database" as DB
Patient -> Web: Select date
Web -> API: GET /api/doctors?date=
API -> DB: Query doctors working
DB --> API: list of doctors
API --> Web: doctors with profiles
Patient -> Web: Select doctor
Web -> API: GET /api/doctors/<id>/availability?date=
API -> DB: Query shifts and appointments
DB --> API: available slots
API --> Web: slots
Patient -> Web: Select slot and request
Web -> API: POST /api/appointments
API -> DB: Create appointment (Pending Review)
DB --> API: success
API --> Web: confirmation
...
actor Doctor
Doctor -> Web: View queue
Web -> API: GET /api/appointments (scoped)
API --> Web: appointment list
Doctor -> Web: Review (confirm/cancel with note)
Web -> API: PATCH /api/appointments/<id>/review
API -> DB: Update status
DB --> API: success
API --> Web: updated
...
Patient -> Web: Reschedule pending
Web -> API: PATCH /api/appointments/<id>/reschedule
API -> DB: Update date/time
DB --> API: success
API --> Web: confirmation
@enduml
